P.M. BRIEFING; 
FREEPORT MCMORAN SELLOFF SET 
Freeport McMoRan Inc. said today it intends to sell at least $750 million in 
assets by the middle of 1991 to reduce its debt. 
The company said it plans to sell at least $600 million of oil and gas 
properties and reduce Freeport-McMoRan Copper Co. Inc.'s ownership in Freeport 
Indonesia Inc. from 91.1% to 80%. 
The company, which has interests in mining and marketing natural resources such 
as sulfur, oil and natural gas, gold and copper, said it expects its long-term 
debt will be about $1.6 billion at the end of the year. 
